Copy of Mikko Ohtamaa's work at http://opensourcehacker.com/2012/05/22/automatically-colorize-terminal-tabs-based-on-the-server-you-are-logged-into/ with minor modification

NOTE: in the following examples PATH == where you want to save color data

For zsh prehook:
1.) Copy into ~/.zsh/bin/
2.) To zshrc add
function precmd {
    python ~/.zsh/rainbow-parade.py PATH
}

For Bash:

1.) Copy into a directory
2.) To bashrc or profile add 
 python ~/dirchosen/rainbow-parade.py PATH

For SSH:

